Floors Castle paintings stolen

POLICE are appealing for information following the theft of two valuable paintings from Floors Castle.
Between 7pm on Sunday and 11.20am on Monday, an area of the castle was entered and the two paintings removed from the wall and stolen.
These paintings are fragile and depict a Highland ox and a sheep.
Police are appealing to anyone who was visiting the castle between these times and saw anything suspicious to contact their local police station.

Last Updated: 30 May 2007
http://www.berwickshiretoday.co.uk/



